Keywords: Age of Apocalypse , Exiles , Generation X , New Mutants , S.W.O.R.D. , Utopia , X-Men
Real Name: Clarice Ferguson
Special Powers
MOVEMENT: Blocking, Characters
BLINK PORTALS: At the beginning of your turn, you may generate a Portal marker [MAX 3] into a square within range -or- place a Portal marker from anywhere on the map into a square within range. // When a friendly character within range and line of fire makes a range attack, they may count range and draw line of fire from a Portal marker. If they do, their maximum range is 3 and after resolutions remove that marker.
BLINK!: Incapacitate. When Blink uses it, after resolutions you may place a hit character given an action token up to 3 squares away from its current square.
MIND IF I BORROW THAT?: Super Senses. // When Blink is missed by an attack, after resolutions you may deal 1 penetrating damage to an opposing character within 3 squares of a Portal marker.

tidge
I really like this dial, and the tricks that this Blink offers to a clever player. (disclosure: I'm pained to write this about a flying HSS piece!). The 75-point cost may push her just over the edge of meta-play, but just as there was once a time when a variety of Avengers/SHIELD teams could wreck house (especially with the Quinjet, even without ID cards) I feel like we are currently in an era where X-Men/SHIELD teams can do the same. My experience with ranged-based teams is that they need to be mobile and have many options for any given round of offense... This Blink contributes her own offense and allows teammates to do the same, which is everything I want in a HeroClix piece.

August 19, 2022
bam
Novel things you can do with BLINK: 1.Run through walls HSS!!! 2.Set up portals around corners. 3.Pair with a plasticity teammate, (Late dial) - Knock your opponent over to them or to a killbox. 4.Evading into delivering 1 penetrating damage. 5.Practically has Phasing & can be an amazing taxi in a pinch late dial. This girl reminds me of MM051 Dagger (69 pts 3 bolts Running Shot Psychic Blast) from back in the day when teamed with a wildcard abuse team (Ultimates, X-men, JSA) not in that Blink has wildcard rather in that she is such an incredible flexible secondary attacker that can hold her own. Is she going up against a swarm? No Problem! How about your opponent's brick? Sure! I would add sidestep to her if you plan on supporting a group to move them to cover & still use an HSS attack.

July 24, 2022
Redrover454
Very cool, very useful piece. Sooo many different fun ways to use her portal markers. You can use them to shoot around corners, as well as extend your friendly's reach. Her dial itself is great too. IM everything + Hypersonic means she will effortlessly zip around any map, and plink away at people with her PS and 3 Bolts. Defensively, Shape and Super is a tried and true combination, with the free point of damage on a miss giving your opponent even more pause before committing to an attack. Blink! gives you intense repositioning that will be sure to drive your opponent crazy. Keep her from getting walloped early on, and Blink should earn her points and then some, especially with a force that can take advantage of her portals!
